Text.Value: Perform the Initialization Procedure:
• Turn the unit OFF.
• Simultaneously press the ALARM and CLR/TEST buttons, then press the ON/OFF button.
• When the 0, 1, 2, appears, release the ALARM and CLR/TEST button. The display should show 000.
• Press the CLR/TEST button once.
• The number 202, followed by 302, and finally 303 should appear on the display.
• When the number 303 appears, turn the unit off.
• This completes the initialization process.
• Perform the Pre-Operational Test Procedure.

Troubleshooting

Perform the Initialization Procedure

  • If a flashing "8" or a flashing "L" appears on the display after performing the pre-operational check, perform the following Initialization procedure.
  • First, turn the unit OFF.
  • Next, simultaneously press the ALARM and CLR/TEST buttons, and while depressed, press the ON/OFF button.
  • Continue to depress the ALARM and CLR/TEST buttons.
  • When the 0, 1, 2, appears, release both the ALARM and CLR/TEST buttons. The display should now show "000".
  • Now, press the CLR/TEST button once.
  • At this time, the number "202" followed momentarily by "302" and finally "303" should appear on the display.
  • When the "303" appears, turn the unit off by pressing the ON/OFF button.
  • This completes the initialization process.
  • After the initialization procedure is complete, perform the preoperational Test Procedure.
  • If the blinking "9" does not appear on the display this time, notify your supervisor.
